description: The molecule is a pyrrolopyrimidine that is 7-methyl-7H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidin-4-amine which has been substituted at position 5 by a 4-fluoro-2,3-dihydro-1H-indol-5-yl group, the nitrogen of which has been acylated by a (6-methylpyridin-2-yl)acetyl group. An orally bioavailable PERK inhibitor. It has a role as an EC 3.1.3.48 (protein-tyrosine-phosphatase) inhibitor, a PERK inhibitor and an antineoplastic agent. It is a pyrrolopyrimidine, a biaryl, a member of indoles, a member of methylpyridines, an organofluorine compound and a tertiary carboxamide.
answer: The molecule is GSK2656157, a pyrrolopyrimidine that is 7-methyl-7H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidin-4-amine, which has been substituted at position 5 by a 4-fluoro-2,3-dihydro-1H-indol-5-yl group, the nitrogen of which has been acylated by a (6-methylpyridin-2-yl)acetyl group. It is an orally bioavailable PERK inhibitor. It has roles as an EC 3.1.3.48 (protein-tyrosine-phosphatase) inhibitor, a PERK inhibitor, and an antineoplastic agent. It is also a pyrrolopyrimidine, a biaryl, a member of indoles, a member of methylpyridines, an organofluorine compound, and a tertiary carboxamide.
